  "texts": [
    "The latter, especially through the Denavit-Hartenberg (DH) parameters, has become the standard in describing robot kinematics due to its computational efficiency.",
    "The DH parameters are widely recognized as the standard method for defining a robot model.",
    "This convention was established by Jacques Denavit and Richard Hartenberg in 1955, with the aim of standardizing coordinate frames for spatial linkages.",
    "Its significance for kinematic analysis of robotic systems was further demonstrated by Richard Paul in 1981.",
    "Despite the development of numerous conventions for attaching reference frames, the DH convention continues to be the preferred method [35] [36]."
  ],
